| year = 2008
| month = March
| pmid = 18301272
| doi = 10.1097/MOG.0b013e3282f3f4c4
| url =
}}</ref> In a large study in the United States, consumption of four or more sugar-sweetened [[soft drinks]] per day gave an [[odds ratio]] of 1.82 for hyperuricemia.<ref name="pmid18163396">{{cite journal
