| journal = Arthritis Rheum.
| volume = 59
| issue = 1
| pages = 109–16
| year = 2008
| month = January
| pmid = 18163396
| doi = 10.1002/art.23245
| url =
}}</ref> Increased production of uric acid is the result of interference, by a product of fructose metabolism, in [[purine metabolism]]. This interference has a dual action, both increasing the conversion of [[adenosine triphosphate|ATP]] to [[inosine]] and hence uric acid and increasing the synthesis of purine.<ref name="pmid8213607">{{cite journal
